Citation.sTitle: The heat capacity of bismuth silicates
Citation.sAbstract: Investigations of the thermodynamic properties of bismuth silicate stable compounds is of practical importance in a viewof their valuable properties. The heat capacity of Bi12SiO20 and Bi4Si3O12 compounds in temperature range from 330K to 1135 K has been determined. The modified Debye function was employed to describe the low-temperature heat capacities, and from the obtained function, the standard entropy, S 298, of bismuth silicates Bi12SiO20 and for Bi4Si3O12were estimated as 15.7 2.2 J/mol atomsK 1 and 13.9 1.5 J/mol atomsK 1, respectively. A three-term Maier Kelley polynomial representation, a + b T + c T 2 was used above 298 K to describe the heat capacity data.
